Untested: `register`, `verifyLogin`, `findByUsername`, `listAccounts`, `getActiveAccount`, `setActiveAccount`, `clearActiveAccount`, `hashPassword` fallback path, `isAccount` guard.

Gaps:
- Password hash fallback (`Web Crypto` unavailable) never exercised — the FNV/djb2 fallback in `hashPassword` (AuthStorageService.ts:70-80) has no coverage and could silently regress.
- `listAccounts` corrupted-JSON / non-array recovery (line ~89-97) untested.
- Duplicate username is case-insensitive (`findByUsername` lowercases) — no test proves `"Budi"` vs `"budi"` collision is caught at register time.
- `verifyLogin` wrong-password vs unknown-username are two different `null` paths — not distinguished by any test.
- `register` boundary lengths (name 2/24, username 3/20, password exactly 6) untested.
- `setActiveAccount` failure path (`safeSet` throwing, e.g. storage quota) never simulated.

```ts
// src/game/services/AuthStorageService.test.ts
import { beforeEach, describe, expect, it, vi } from 'vitest';
import { AuthStorageService } from './AuthStorageService';

describe('AuthStorageService', () => {
    beforeEach(() => window.localStorage.clear());

    it('registers a valid account and can log in with it', async () => {
        const result = await AuthStorageService.register('Budi Santoso', 'budi', 'rahasia');
        expect(result.ok).toBe(true);

        const loggedIn = await AuthStorageService.verifyLogin('budi', 'rahasia');
        expect(loggedIn?.username).toBe('budi');
    });

    it('rejects duplicate username case-insensitively', async () => {
        await AuthStorageService.register('Budi', 'budi', 'rahasia');
        const dup = await AuthStorageService.register('Budi Lain', 'BUDI', 'rahasia2');
        expect(dup.ok).toBe(false);
    });

    it.each([
        ['a', 'toolong-username-min3', 'rahasia', /Nama lengkap/],
        ['Budi', 'ab', 'rahasia', /Nama panggilan/],
        ['Budi', 'budi', '12345', /Password/]
    ])('rejects invalid input: %s/%s/%s', async (name, uname, pass, msg) => {
        const r = await AuthStorageService.register(name, uname, pass);
        expect(r.ok).toBe(false);
        if (!r.ok) expect(r.error).toMatch(msg);
    });

    it('verifyLogin returns null for wrong password vs unknown user', async () => {
        await AuthStorageService.register('Budi', 'budi', 'rahasia');
        expect(await AuthStorageService.verifyLogin('budi', 'salah')).toBeNull();
        expect(await AuthStorageService.verifyLogin('nobody', 'rahasia')).toBeNull();
    });

    it('recovers from corrupted localStorage JSON', () => {
        window.localStorage.setItem('sikapandawa.accounts', '{not json');
        expect(AuthStorageService.listAccounts()).toEqual([]);
    });

    it('getActiveAccount returns null when active id points to a removed account', () => {
        window.localStorage.setItem('sikapandawa.activeAccountId', 'ghost-id');
        expect(AuthStorageService.getActiveAccount()).toBeNull();
    });

    it('falls back to non-crypto hash when window.crypto.subtle is unavailable', async () => {
        const original = window.crypto.subtle;
        // @ts-expect-error simulating missing SubtleCrypto
        delete window.crypto.subtle;
        const result = await AuthStorageService.register('Budi', 'budi', 'rahasia');
        expect(result.ok).toBe(true);
        window.crypto.subtle = original;
    });
});
```

