Untested: `recordLevelResult`, `sanitize` (via `getProgress`), `totalStars`, `hasSeenIntro`/`markIntroSeen`, `createInitialProgress`.

Gaps:
- **"Best score tidak pernah turun"** (Game Bible rule) — no test proves a lower `runStars` doesn't overwrite a higher stored best.
- Unlock never regresses — no test for replaying an already-unlocked level with 0 stars.
- `runStars` clamping (`Math.max(0, Math.min(3, ...))`) untested for out-of-range/float input (e.g. `-1`, `3.9`, `NaN`).
- `sanitize` migration path (old data missing `introSeen`) untested — this is explicitly called out in the code comment as a migration concern.
- `sanitize` with `levelStars` containing non-numeric or out-of-range values untested.
- Last level (`TOTAL_LEVELS`) never unlocks a `TOTAL_LEVELS + 1` — boundary untested.
- `markIntroSeen` idempotency (calling twice doesn't duplicate) untested.

```ts
// src/game/services/ProgressStorageService.test.ts
import { beforeEach, describe, expect, it } from 'vitest';
import { ProgressStorageService, TOTAL_LEVELS } from './ProgressStorageService';

const ACCOUNT = 'acc-1';

describe('ProgressStorageService', () => {
    beforeEach(() => window.localStorage.clear());

    it('best score never decreases', () => {
        ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, 3);
        const outcome = ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, 1);
        expect(outcome.bestStars).toBe(3);
        expect(outcome.isNewBest).toBe(false);
    });

    it('unlocks next level on first star, only once', () => {
        const first = ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, 1);
        expect(first.unlockedLevel).toBe(2);
        const second = ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, 2);
        expect(second.unlockedLevel).toBeNull(); // already unlocked
    });

    it('does not unlock beyond TOTAL_LEVELS', () => {
        const outcome = ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, TOTAL_LEVELS, 3);
        expect(outcome.unlockedLevel).toBeNull();
    });

    it('clamps out-of-range runStars', () => {
        expect(ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, -5).runStars).toBe(0);
        expect(ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, 99).runStars).toBe(3);
    });

    it('sanitize migrates legacy data missing introSeen', () => {
        window.localStorage.setItem(
            'sikapandawa.progress.acc-1',
            JSON.stringify({ highestUnlockedLevel: 2, levelStars: { 1: 3 } })
        );
        const progress = ProgressStorageService.getProgress(ACCOUNT);
        expect(progress.introSeen).toEqual([]);
        expect(progress.highestUnlockedLevel).toBe(2);
    });

    it('markIntroSeen is idempotent', () => {
        ProgressStorageService.markIntroSeen(ACCOUNT, 'yudhistira');
        ProgressStorageService.markIntroSeen(ACCOUNT, 'yudhistira');
        expect(ProgressStorageService.getProgress(ACCOUNT).introSeen).toEqual(['yudhistira']);
    });

    it('totalStars sums across all levels', () => {
        ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, 2);
        ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 2, 3);
        expect(ProgressStorageService.totalStars(ProgressStorageService.getProgress(ACCOUNT))).toBe(5);
    });
});
