No logic here, but these are hand-authored narrative/answer datasets where a typo is a silent content bug (wrong `correctChoiceId`, dangling `speaker` key, out-of-bounds `x`). Currently the only thing catching mistakes is manual playtesting.

Gaps:
- Nothing asserts `LEVELS[1]`/`LEVELS[2]` correct-answer sequence matches the Game Bible (`C,A,B` / `C,C,A`) — this is the single most important content invariant in the project (CLAUDE.md calls it out explicitly) and has zero regression protection.
- Nothing asserts every `dialog[].speaker` / `feedback[key].speaker` exists in `SPEAKERS_LV1`/`SPEAKERS_LV2`.
- Nothing asserts `feedback` has an entry for every `choices[].id`.
- Nothing asserts actor/object `x` placements stay within `minPlayerX`/`maxPlayerX`/`worldWidth`.

```ts
// src/game/data/levels.test.ts
import { describe, expect, it } from 'vitest';
import { LEVELS, SPEAKERS_LV1, SPEAKERS_LV2, speakersFor } from './levels';

describe('LEVELS data integrity', () => {
    it('Level 1 correct answers match the Game Bible (C, A, B)', () => {
        const ids = LEVELS[1].segments
            .flatMap((s) => s.interactions)
            .filter((i) => i.question)
            .map((i) => i.question!.correctChoiceId);
        expect(ids).toEqual(['C', 'A', 'B']);
    });

    it('Level 2 correct answers match the Game Bible (C, C, A)', () => {
        const ids = LEVELS[2].segments
            .flatMap((s) => s.interactions)
            .filter((i) => i.question)
            .map((i) => i.question!.correctChoiceId);
        expect(ids).toEqual(['C', 'C', 'A']);
    });

    it.each([1, 2])('level %i: every dialog/feedback speaker is registered', (levelId) => {
        const speakers = speakersFor(levelId);
        for (const seg of LEVELS[levelId].segments) {
            for (const i of seg.interactions) {
                for (const line of i.dialog) {
                    expect(speakers).toHaveProperty(line.speaker);
                }
                if (i.question) {
                    for (const fb of Object.values(i.question.feedback)) {
                        expect(speakers).toHaveProperty(fb.speaker);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    });

    it.each([1, 2])('level %i: every choice id has a feedback entry', (levelId) => {
        for (const seg of LEVELS[levelId].segments) {
            for (const i of seg.interactions) {
                if (!i.question) continue;
                for (const choice of i.question.choices) {
                    expect(i.question.feedback[choice.id]).toBeDefined();
                }
            }
        }
    });

    it.each([1, 2])('level %i: interaction/actor positions stay within player bounds', (levelId) => {
        for (const seg of LEVELS[levelId].segments) {
            for (const i of seg.interactions) {
                expect(i.triggerX).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(seg.minPlayerX);
                expect(i.triggerX).toBeLessThanOrEqual(seg.maxPlayerX);
            }
        }
    });
});
```

